candidates.title: Code for v0.0.15
candidates.body:
This PR includes the following:

1. PR from @ddnomad to allow access to `HttpData` from `ParsingErrorInfo`. #39 
2. Adding a debug message with the query URL. #40 
3. Making `eventDate` optional. #41 
4. Moving to Rust's own `is_terminal`. #23 
5. Fixing of some lints.
6. Updating of all dependencies of significance.
7. Rework of the bootstrapping code to make it accessible to callers of the client library.
8. Some documentation and re-exports in the client library.

candidates.title: Andy dev
candidates.body: This PR covers a rework of the bootstrapping codebase so that it can be used by calling code of the client library.

candidates.title: Andy dev
candidates.body: This PR has updates to all dependencies of significance.

candidates.title: Lints and docs
candidates.body: This PR contains small changes to address lints in the new rust-analyzer and documents the release process.

candidates.title: Upgrade to 0.0.14
candidates.body:
This PR includes:

1. Changes to clap help colors to match clap v3 help output
2. new rdap-srv-test-data command to generate test data for load testing
3. drill.yaml for using Drill to load test the server
4. change from using pinboard to using arc<tokio::rwlock> to fix memory leak
5. support for RDAP /help queries in rdap-srv and tools.

candidates.title: removed pinboard in the server
candidates.body: This PR removes pinboard in favor of tokio's rwlock. No performance differences can be measured with drill load test, and less memory is used.

candidates.title: Minus 5.4 and Bootstrapping in SRV
candidates.body:
This PR does two things:
1. Upgrades minus to 5.4 in the CLI which fixes a bug causing an extra line to be emitted.
2. Adds the capability to be a bootstrap server to SRV.

candidates.title: Bug fixes and some small fixes
candidates.body:
* `--help` now has information on where the cache is stored.
* fixed autnum bootstrapping bug
* fixed a cache bug that prevented non-Entity object classes from being deserialized from cache
* add `rdap_type` to the `--json-extra` output to help scripts determine the rdap object class
* added common parsing example
* a lot of cleanup and changes to the internal common API
* support for cidr0 extension
* moved from simplelog to tracing-subscriber for the cli
* README updates

* Removes the `--url` flag in favor url query detection.
* Adds insecure connection options
* Fixes bug where bootstrapping was preventing url queries

candidates.title: Caching and Bootstrapping
candidates.body: This PR delivers on two major features, result caching and bootstrapping.

candidates.title: Release to 0.0.9
candidates.body:
In this release:

* a bunch of specwarning, specerror, and info checks
* README files for the individual crates
* new --reset parameter
* other code refactorings

candidates.title: Dev
candidates.body: Updates the workspace dependency version numbers is the individual crates. Also adds some categories.

candidates.title: Dev
candidates.body:
This merge addresses upgrades to reqwest which forces and upgrade of openssl which eliminates some vulnerabilities.
Additionally, default features are removed from chrono, eliminating the use of the time crate which also has a vulnerability.
This merge bumps the version to 0.0.8

candidates.title: Update to version 0.0.7
candidates.body: Merging of this branch will address 7 issues, adds new testing mechanisms, new tests, and some new features, mostly more RDAP specification checks and a directory feature for rdap-srv-data
